Hi, @qiaojiang2:
First, I suggest you update your code that is not up-to-date.
And, from you stack log. I guess it's because mysql user do not have enought right or mysql version is unexpected.

you can check it.

use current mysql user execute this sql, see what result return.

```sql
SHOW MASTER STATUS;
SHOW VARIABLES LIKE 'server_id';
SHOW VARIABLES LIKE 'version';
```

@cobstergo Hi
4.1.1 does not have better support for `subquery`, I suggest you try the `master branch`.
Besides, it is required that `table_budev ` and `table_ticket ` have the same sharding algorithm.

@hand515 Thanks for your answer. :)
@Simbafa Thanks for your attention, I will consider focusing on this enhancement after I finish #6466 .
We will include #6212 in our next release. 

Trista

